{title: Chew Tobacco Rag}
{artist: Pee Wee King}
{composer: Written by Billy Briggs}

[G]Well I like to smoke my old corn pipe
But I've chewed tobacco nearly [D7]all my [G]life
P-ting putune p-tine p-ting putune
Chew tobacco chew tobacco [D7]chew tobacco [G]rag
I like to smoke cigarettes sometimes
But when it comes to dippin' [D7]I draw the [G]line
Repeat #2
If you chew tobacco don't spit on the floor
Expectorate [D7]in the cuspi[G]dor
Repeat #2
If you never had a chew in your life before
Why don't you try cause you're [D7]sure to want [G]more
Repeat #2
Just get a big plug and you bite off the end
And let it run down and [D7]off of your [G]chin
Repeat #2
You can smoke cigarettes while the sun goes down
But I'll chew tobacco and I'll [D7]spit on the [G]ground
Repeat #2
Now all day long you can smoke your pipe
But I'll chew tobacco and I'll [D7]spit all [G]night
Repeat #2
I like to smoke cigarettes sometimes
But when it comes to dippin' there [D7]I draw the [G]line
Repeat #2